olive oil
1 cob corn
1 tomato
1 packet Mild Chorizo
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
1 tsp brown sugar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Coriander

• Slice kernels off corn cob.
• Finely chop tomato.
• Cut mild chorizo into 1cm chunks.
• In a small bowl, combine garlic aioli and mild chipotle sauce.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Add chorizo and corn and cook until browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add brown sugar and cook until caramelised, 1-2 minutes.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are “popping” out.

• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts until
warmed through.
• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, tomato and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Fill tortillas with zingy salad, caramelised chorizo and charred corn.
• Drizzle over chipotle aioli.
• Tear over coriander to serve. Enjoy!